{"type":"user","uuid":"e520a00e-944a-4943-aae8-7263b0521812","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2ef7192f20a5468d8c856404","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n   2→MODULE: pipeline\n   3→PATH: dev-pipeline/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: automation scripts + templates for feature/bugfix pipelines\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- dev-pipeline/run.sh\n   8→- dev-pipeline/run-bugfix.sh\n   9→- dev-pipeline/launch-daemon.sh\n  10→- dev-pipeline/launch-bugfix-daemon.sh\n  11→- dev-pipeline/retry-feature.sh\n  12→- dev-pipeline/retry-bug.sh\n  13→- dev-pipeline/reset-feature.sh\n  14→- dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py\n  15→- dev-pipeline/scripts/*.py\n  16→- dev-pipeline/templates/*\n  17→\n  18→STATE_PATHS:\n  19→- dev-pipeline/state/\n  20→- dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/\n  21→\n  22→DAEMON_LOG_POLICY:\n  23→- feature daemon log -> dev-pipeline/state/pipeline-daemon.log\n  24→- bugfix daemon log -> dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/pipeline-daemon.log\n  25→\n  26→TRAPS:\n  27→- several large operational scripts (>500 lines) require cautious edits\n  28→- TODO density is concentrated in this module\n  29→\n  30→SUBDIRS:\n  31→- dev-pipeline/scripts -> .prizm-docs/pipeline/scripts.prizm\n  32→\n  33→DECISIONS:\n  34→- 2026-03-09 | pipeline-doc-init | treat shell+python pipeline as independent module\n  35→- 2026-03-10 | f001-path-policy-shared | centralize feature/bug/session/session-status/daemon-log paths via scripts/path_policy.py and JS mirror module\n  36→- 2026-03-10 | f001-us3-scope | include logs/reset in runner+service API surface using daemon wrappers and clean reset commands\n  37→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ae3e7667d5ac48f881c2ce4c","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:36:03.720Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"064ad008-622e-43c7-a83d-822f7e3a89fa","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6b922f08a98e4722b3b43484","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n   2→MODULE: runtime\n   3→PATH: src/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/config.js\n  11→- src/http/server.js\n  12→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n  13→- src/services/chat-service.js\n  14→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  15→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n  16→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n  17→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n  18→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n  19→- src/bot/telegram.js\n  20→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n  21→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n  22→\n  23→SUBDIRS:\n  24→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n  25→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n  26→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n  27→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n  28→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n  29→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n  30→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n  31→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n  32→\n  33→INTERFACES:\n  34→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n  35→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, text message relay\n  36→\n  37→TRAPS:\n  38→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n  39→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n  40→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n  41→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n  42→\n  43→DECISIONS:\n  44→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n  45→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n  46→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n  47→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n  48→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ae3e7667d5ac48f881c2ce4c","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:36:03.721Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"e27a3da2-cdf3-4f19-b101-4817d0e8ad43","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_014ede917f21423daf4b6379","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-001: Project Infrastructure Setup\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→为 Telegram 管道模式建立统一的工程基线，确保后续命令路由与 pipeline 控制能力有稳定的运行基础。\n   6→\n   7→## User Stories\n   8→\n   9→### US-1: 统一配置加载与校验\n  10→\n  11→**As a** 系统开发者  \n  12→**I want** 通过单一入口加载所有配置并在缺失关键配置时获得可读错误  \n  13→**So that** 我可以快速定位配置问题而非遇到难以理解的运行时错误\n  14→\n  15→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  16→- AC-1.1: `loadPipelineInfraConfig()` 返回冻结的配置对象\n  17→- AC-1.2: 缺失必需字段时抛出结构化错误（含 code、hint，字段信息在 context.field 中）\n  18→- AC-1.3: 支持 ENV 与 CLI 参数覆盖，CLI 优先\n  19→\n  20→### US-2: 标准目录结构与命名规则\n  21→\n  22→**As a** 运维人员  \n  23→**I want** 所有计划文件、状态文件、日志文件有统一的目录结构与命名规则  \n  24→**So that** 我可以快速定位问题并执行运维操作\n  25→\n  26→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  27→- AC-2.1: feature specs 存放于 `.prizmkit/specs/{slug}/`\n  28→- AC-2.2: feature state 存放于 `dev-pipeline/state/features/{F-NNN}/`\n  29→- AC-2.3: session logs 存放于 `dev-pipeline/state/features/{F-NNN}/sessions/{sessionId}/logs/`\n  30→- AC-2.4: daemon logs 分别存放于:\n  31→  - feature daemon: `dev-pipeline/state/pipeline-daemon.log`\n  32→  - bugfix daemon: `dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/pipeline-daemon.log`\n  33→\n  34→### US-3: 脚本入口封装\n  35→\n  36→**As a** 控制层开发者  \n  37→**I want** 通过统一的 JS 函数调用 dev-pipeline 脚本  \n  38→**So that** 我可以在 Telegram handler 中可靠地执行 pipeline 操作\n  39→\n  40→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  41→- AC-3.1: `buildPipelineCommand()` 构造正确的脚本路径与参数\n  42→- AC-3.2: `executePipelineCommand()` 执行脚本并返回标准化结果\n  43→- AC-3.3: 支持 run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset 操作\n  44→\n  45→### US-4: TypeScript 构建与静态检查\n  46→\n  47→**As a** 项目维护者  \n  48→**I want** 基础构建与静态检查流程可运行  \n  49→**So that** 我可以在渐进迁移过程中保证代码质量\n  50→\n  51→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  52→- AC-4.1: `npm run typecheck` 成功执行且不破坏现有流程\n  53→- AC-4.2: `npm run lint` 成功执行\n  54→- AC-4.3: tsconfig.json 包含 pipeline-infra 与 pipeline-control-service\n  55→\n  56→## Scope\n  57→\n  58→### In Scope\n  59→- 配置加载与校验 (`src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js`)\n  60→- 路径策略模块 (`src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js`)\n  61→- 错误码定义 (`src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`)\n  62→- 脚本运行器 (`src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js`)\n  63→- Python 路径策略镜像 (`dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py`)\n  64→- TypeScript 配置 (`tsconfig.json`)\n  65→- 单元测试覆盖\n  66→\n  67→### Out of Scope\n  68→- 历史代码的完整 TypeScript 迁移\n  69→- Telegram 命令路由（F-002）\n  70→- 进程控制器高层 API（F-004）\n  71→\n  72→## Dependencies\n  73→\n  74→- 无外部依赖（基础设施功能）\n  75→\n  76→## Risks\n  77→\n  78→| Risk | Mitigation |\n  79→|------|------------|\n  80→| 配置加载逻辑复杂导致难以调试 | 保持函数纯度，添加详细测试用例 |\n  81→| Python/JS 路径策略不同步 | 建立兼容性测试确保行为一致 |\n  82→| TypeScript 配置过于严格阻塞开发 | 初始 strict: false，渐进收紧 |\n  83→\n  84→## Non-Functional Requirements\n  85→\n  86→- **性能**: 配置加载在 10ms 内完成\n  87→- **可维护性**: 每个模块单文件，函数长度 < 100 行\n  88→- **测试覆盖**: 核心模块 > 90% 分支覆盖\n  89→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ae3e7667d5ac48f881c2ce4c","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:36:03.721Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"1f0fa1e8-0a64-4b83-81ca-676c9e05c552","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e0a4df1f02e54a108eb5ddeb","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-002: Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→在 Telegram Bot 中新增管道控制命令路由层，支持解析与分发 `/pipeline`、`/bugfix`、`/planner`、`/status`、`/logs`、`/stop` 等命令，将参数规范化后交给后端控制模块执行。\n   6→\n   7→**Scope**: 命令语义解析、参数验证、权限检查、路由分发。不包含长任务执行。\n   8→\n   9→**Dependencies**: F-001 (Project Infrastructure Setup) — completed\n  10→\n  11→---\n  12→\n  13→## User Stories\n  14→\n  15→### US-1: Pipeline Command\n  16→作为授权用户，我可以使用 `/pipeline [action] [target]` 命令启动或查询 feature 管道。\n  17→\n  18→**Note**: `/planner` 命令作为 `/pipeline` 的管道类型变体（type=planner），行为相同，故包含在本 US 范围内（见 D1）。\n  19→\n  20→**Example**:\n  21→- `/pipeline run my-feature` — 启动管道\n  22→- `/pipeline status` — 查询状态\n  23→- `/pipeline logs my-feature` — 查看日志\n  24→- `/planner run my-feature` — 启动 planner 类型管道\n  25→\n  26→**Acceptance**:\n  27→- 支持 `run`, `status`, `logs`, `stop` 子命令\n  28→- `target` 参数可选，默认当前工作目录\n  29→- 无效子命令返回帮助提示\n  30→- `/planner` 行为等同于 `/pipeline --type=planner`\n  31→\n  32→---\n  33→\n  34→### US-2: Bugfix Command\n  35→作为授权用户，我可以使用 `/bugfix [target]` 快捷命令启动 bugfix 管道。\n  36→\n  37→**Example**:\n  38→- `/bugfix session-123` — 启动 bugfix 管道\n  39→\n  40→**Acceptance**:\n  41→- 等同于 `/pipeline run --type=bugfix <target>`\n  42→- 参数缺失时返回使用说明\n  43→\n  44→---\n  45→\n  46→### US-3: Status Query\n  47→作为授权用户，我可以使用 `/status` 查看当前管道状态。\n  48→\n  49→**Example**:\n  50→- `/status` — 显示所有运行中的管道\n  51→\n  52→**Acceptance**:\n  53→- 返回管道列表 + 状态摘要\n  54→- 无运行管道时返回提示\n  55→\n  56→---\n  57→\n  58→### US-4: Logs Query\n  59→作为授权用户，我可以使用 `/logs [target]` 查看管道日志。\n  60→\n  61→**Example**:\n  62→- `/logs` — 最近管道日志\n  63→- `/logs session-123` — 指定目标日志\n  64→\n  65→**Acceptance**:\n  66→- 支持分页或截断显示\n  67→- 日志过长时发送为文件\n  68→\n  69→---\n  70→\n  71→### US-5: Stop Pipeline\n  72→作为授权用户，我可以使用 `/stop [target]` 停止运行中的管道。\n  73→\n  74→**Example**:\n  75→- `/stop` — 停止当前管道\n  76→- `/stop session-123` — 停止指定管道\n  77→\n  78→**Acceptance**:\n  79→- 确认停止操作\n  80→- 返回停止结果\n  81→\n  82→---\n  83→\n  84→### US-6: Error Guidance\n  85→作为用户，当我输入错误参数时，系统返回明确的修正建议。\n  86→\n  87→**Example**:\n  88→- `/pipeline xyz` → \"未知子命令 'xyz'。可用: run, status, logs, stop\"\n  89→\n  90→**Acceptance**:\n  91→- 参数错误有明确提示\n  92→- 提供正确的命令示例\n  93→\n  94→---\n  95→\n  96→### US-7: Authorization Guard\n  97→作为未授权用户，我无法调用管道命令，且收到统一拒绝提示。\n  98→\n  99→**Acceptance**:\n 100→- 所有管道命令需授权检查\n 101→- 统一拒绝消息（不暴露敏感信息）\n 102→\n 103→---\n 104→\n 105→## Non-Functional Requirements\n 106→\n 107→### NFR-1: Extensibility\n 108→- 命令路由层支持注册新命令\n 109→- 参数解析器可扩展\n 110→\n 111→### NFR-2: Testability\n 112→- Handler 接口可 mock\n 113→- 权限检查可 mock\n 114→\n 115→### NFR-3: Performance\n 116→- 命令解析 < 50ms\n 117→- 不阻塞 Telegram webhook\n 118→\n 119→---\n 120→\n 121→## Scope Boundaries\n 122→\n 123→### In Scope\n 124→- 命令解析与路由\n 125→- 参数规范化\n 126→- 权限检查\n 127→- 帮助文本生成\n 128→- 错误提示\n 129→\n 130→### Out of Scope\n 131→- 长任务执行（由 pipeline-control-service 处理）\n 132→- Pipeline 内部逻辑\n 133→- 持久化存储\n 134→- Web UI\n 135→\n 136→---\n 137→\n 138→## Command Reference\n 139→\n 140→| Command | Subcommands | Params | Handler |\n 141→|---------|-------------|--------|---------|\n 142→| `/pipeline` | run, status, logs, stop | `[target]`, `[--type=]` | pipelineHandler |\n 143→| `/bugfix` | — | `<target>` | bugfixHandler |\n 144→| `/planner` | run, status, logs | `[target]` | plannerHandler |\n 145→| `/status` | — | — | statusHandler |\n 146→| `/logs` | — | `[target]` | logsHandler |\n 147→| `/stop` | — | `[target]` | stopHandler |\n 148→\n 149→---\n 150→\n 151→## Alias Mapping\n 152→\n 153→| Alias | Maps To |\n 154→|-------|---------|\n 155→| `/p` | `/pipeline` |\n 156→| `/b` | `/bugfix` |\n 157→| `/s` | `/status` |\n 158→| `/l` | `/logs` |\n 159→\n 160→---\n 161→\n 162→## Decisions\n 163→\n 164→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 165→|----|------|----------|\n 166→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | `/planner` 为独立管道类型，行为同 `/pipeline`，默认 `type=planner` |\n 167→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 复用现有 `isAllowedUser()` 进行授权检查，分级权限留作后续扩展 |\n 168→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 日志 < 4000 字符分块发送，>= 4000 字符发送为文件 |\n 169→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ae3e7667d5ac48f881c2ce4c","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:36:03.722Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"4290d428-ea85-4cfc-b9b2-49341b2abd52","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0be81e69db43472d98349883","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Feature Registry\n   2→\n   3→| ID | Slug | Title | Status | Last Updated |\n   4→|----|------|-------|--------|--------------|\n   5→| F-001 | 001-project-infrastructure-setup | Project Infrastructure Setup | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   6→| F-002 | 002-telegram-pipeline-command-router | Telegram Pipeline Command Router | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   7→| F-003 | 003-feature-and-bug-plan-ingestion | Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion | completed | 2026-03-12 |\n   8→\n   9→## F-001: Project Infrastructure Setup\n  10→\n  11→**Status:** completed  \n  12→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  13→\n  14→### Deliverables\n  15→\n  16→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Unified config loading with ENV/CLI override\n  17→- `src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js` - Feature/bug/session path resolution\n  18→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Error code definitions and factories\n  19→- `src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js` - Script execution wrapper\n  20→- `src/pipeline-infra/index.js` - Module entry point\n  21→- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - High-level pipeline control API\n  22→- `dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py` - Python path policy mirror\n  23→- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/` and `tests/services/`\n  24→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f001-user-stories.integration.test.js`\n  25→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm` and `.prizm-docs/pipeline/scripts.prizm`\n  26→\n  27→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  28→\n  29→- US-1: Unified config loading with readable validation errors\n  30→- US-2: Standard directory structure with Python/JS parity\n  31→- US-3: Unified script execution API (run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset)\n  32→- US-4: TypeScript and ESLint baseline established\n  33→\n  34→### Verification\n  35→\n  36→- `npm run typecheck`: 0 errors\n  37→- `npm run lint`: 0 warnings\n  38→- `npm test`: 29 tests pass\n  39→\n  40→---\n  41→\n  42→## F-002: Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n  43→\n  44→**Status:** completed  \n  45→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  46→\n  47→### Deliverables\n  48→\n  49→- `src/bot/commands/index.js` - Router entry point (auth, parse, validate, dispatch)\n  50→- `src/bot/commands/parser.js` - Command parsing with alias support\n  51→- `src/bot/commands/registry.js` - Dynamic command registration\n  52→- `src/bot/commands/validator.js` - Parameter validation\n  53→- `src/bot/commands/formatter.js` - User-friendly error messages\n  54→- `src/bot/commands/help.js` - Dynamic help text generation\n  55→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Pipeline command handler\n  56→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` - Bugfix shortcut handler\n  57→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js` - Planner pipeline handler\n  58→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Status query handler\n  59→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Logs query handler\n  60→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Stop pipeline handler\n  61→- Unit tests in `tests/bot/commands/`\n  62→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f002-command-router.integration.test.js`\n  63→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm`\n  64→\n  65→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  66→\n  67→- US-1: Pipeline command with run/status/logs/stop subcommands\n  68→- US-2: Bugfix command as shortcut to `/pipeline run --type=bugfix`\n  69→- US-3: Status query showing all running pipelines\n  70→- US-4: Logs query with file fallback for large output\n  71→- US-5: Stop pipeline with confirmation\n  72→- US-6: Error guidance with clear suggestions\n  73→- US-7: Authorization guard on all commands\n  74→\n  75→### Commands Implemented\n  76→\n  77→| Command | Aliases | Description |\n  78→|---------|---------|-------------|\n  79→| `/pipeline` | `/p` | Manage pipelines (run/status/logs/stop) |\n  80→| `/bugfix` | `/b` | Start bugfix pipeline |\n  81→| `/planner` | — | Manage planner pipelines |\n  82→| `/status` | `/s` | Show running pipelines |\n  83→| `/logs` | `/l` | View pipeline logs |\n  84→| `/stop` | — | Stop running pipelines |\n  85→\n  86→### Verification\n  87→\n  88→- `npm test`: 105 tests pass (76 for F-002)\n  89→- Code review: PASS\n  90→- All 21 tasks completed\n  91→\n  92→---\n  93→\n  94→## F-003: Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion\n  95→\n  96→**Status:** completed  \n  97→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  98→\n  99→### Deliverables\n 100→\n 101→- `src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js` - Schema validation, version management, plan registry\n 102→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js` - Plan command handler (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n 103→- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Document upload handler for JSON files\n 104→- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - Extended with resolvePlanListPath()\n 105→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Extended with plansDir config\n 106→- `plans/` directory structure with feature-list/ and bug-fix-list/ subdirectories\n 107→- Unit tests in `tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js`\n 108→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f003-plan-ingestion.integration.test.js`\n 109→\n 110→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 111→\n 112→- US-1: Upload Plan File - Telegram document message handling with auto-type detection\n 113→- US-2: Schema Validation - Ajv-based validation with field-level error messages\n 114→- US-3: Version Management - Timestamp-based versioning with use/rollback commands\n 115→- US-4: Plan Status Query - Status command showing version info and content summary\n 116→- US-5: Plan Integrity Protection - Validation precedes save, current version preserved on error\n 117→- US-6: Pipeline Integration - resolvePlanListPath() for dynamic plan path resolution\n 118→\n 119→### Commands Implemented\n 120→\n 121→| Command | Subcommands | Description |\n 122→|---------|-------------|-------------|\n 123→| `/plan` | status, versions, use, rollback, validate | Manage plan files |\n 124→\n 125→### Verification\n 126→\n 127→- Code review: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n 128→- All 18 tasks completed\n 129→- Unit tests: 19 passing\n 130→- Integration tests: 10 passing\n 131→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ae3e7667d5ac48f881c2ce4c","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:36:03.722Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
