{"type":"user","uuid":"76066fc8-1f41-4246-8a3e-2cab927cdc28","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_345369362686478a9271975a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Updated task #2 status"}],"is_error":false,"_meta":{"rawResponse":{"task":{"subject":"Run prizmkit.plan to create plan.md","description":"Step 2: Create technical implementation plan for F-004. Define architecture, component design, interface design (API specs, data models), module dependencies, testing strategy, and risk assessment. Map each user story to planned components.","activeForm":"Creating technical plan","status":"in_progress","id":"2","createdAt":1773257814734,"updatedAt":1773257880260},"todos":[{"content":"Run prizmkit.specify to create spec.md","activeForm":"Creating feature specification","status":"completed"},{"content":"Run prizmkit.plan to create plan.md","activeForm":"Creating technical plan","status":"in_progress"},{"content":"Run prizmkit.tasks to create tasks.md","activeForm":"Decomposing into tasks","status":"pending"}]},"renderer":{"type":"todo"}}}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ae3e7667d5ac48f881c2ce4c","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:38:00.277Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603120338006c922cdc75c44774","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"id":"202603120338006c922cdc75c44774","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_97ef40262fd642a19371d02d","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-004: Pipeline Process Controller — Technical Plan\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Telegram Command Router (F-002)                      │\n│                    src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js                            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                      │\n                                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Pipeline Controller (NEW)                               │\n│                    src/services/pipeline-controller.js                       │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │ • startPipeline()  • stopPipeline()  • retryTarget()                │    │\n│  │ • runSingle()      • getStatus()      • getLogs()                   │    │\n│  │ • forceUnlock()    • acquireLock()    • releaseLock()               │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                    │                      │                      │\n                    ▼                      ▼                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────────┐\n│    Lock Manager (NEW)   │ │   State Manager (NEW)   │ │   Script Runner     │\n│  src/pipeline-infra/    │ │  src/pipeline-infra/    │ │    (Existing)       │\n│    lock-manager.js      │ │    state-manager.js     │ │  script-runner.js   │\n├─────────────────────────┤ ├─────────────────────────┤ ├─────────────────────┤\n│ • acquireLock()         │ │ • readDaemonMeta()      │ │ • buildPipelineCmd()│\n│ • releaseLock()         │ │ • readPipelineState()   │ │ • executePipeline() │\n│ • isLocked()            │ │ • readCurrentSession()  │ │ • normalizeResult() │\n│ • forceUnlock()         │ │ • writeDaemonMeta()     │ │                     │\n│ • validateLock()        │ │ • getLastResult()       │ │                     │\n└─────────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────────┘ └─────────────────────┘\n                    │                      │                      │\n                    └──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┘\n                                           ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                    │                  dev-pipeline/scripts/                  │\n                    │  launch-daemon.sh, launch-bugfix-daemon.sh              │\n                    │  run.sh, run-bugfix.sh, retry-*.sh, reset-*.sh          │\n                    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                           │\n                                           ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                    │                       State Files                       │\n                    │  state/.pipeline.pid, state/pipeline.json               │\n                    │  state/.pipeline-meta.json, state/pipeline-daemon.log   │\n                    │  bugfix-state/... (mirror structure)                    │\n                    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Component Design\n\n### 2.1 Pipeline Controller (`src/services/pipeline-controller.js`)\n\n**职责**: 高层控制 API 入口，协调 lock-manager、state-manager、script-runner\n\n**核心方法**:\n\n```javascript\nexport function createPipelineController(options = {}) {\n  const {\n    lockManager = createLockManager(),\n    stateManager = createStateManager(),\n    scriptRunner = executePipelineCommand,\n    config = loadPipelineInfraConfig()\n  } = options;\n\n  return {\n    // Lifecycle\n    startPipeline(params),\n    stopPipeline(params),\n    \n    // Target Operations\n    retryTarget(params),\n    runSingle(params),\n    \n    // Query\n    getStatus(params),\n    getLogs(params),\n    \n    // Admin\n    forceUnlock(params),\n    \n    // Internal\n    _acquireLock(type),\n    _releaseLock(type),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Lock Manager (`src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js`)\n\n**职责**: 并发锁管理，防止同类型管道同时运行\n\n**实现策略**: 文件锁 + PID 校验\n- 锁文件: `state/.pipeline.lock` / `bugfix-state/.pipeline.lock`\n- 锁内容: `{ pid, acquiredAt, type }`\n- 校验: 检查锁文件 + 验证 PID 是否存活\n\n**核心方法**:\n\n```javascript\nexport function createLockManager(options = {}) {\n  const { config = loadPipelineInfraConfig() } = options;\n  \n  return {\n    async acquireLock(type, pid = process.pid),\n    async releaseLock(type, pid = process.pid),\n    async isLocked(type),\n    async validateLock(type),\n    async forceUnlock(type),\n    async getLockInfo(type),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 State Manager (`src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js`)\n\n**职责**: 读取和管理管道状态文件\n\n**核心方法**:\n\n```javascript\nexport function createStateManager(options = {}) {\n  const { config = loadPipelineInfraConfig() } = options;\n  \n  return {\n    // Read Operations\n    async readDaemonMeta(type),\n    async readPipelineState(type),\n    async readCurrentSession(type),\n    async getLastResult(type),\n    \n    // Write Operations\n    async writeDaemonMeta(type, meta),\n    async writeLastResult(type, result),\n    \n    // Query\n    async isDaemonRunning(type),\n    async getDaemonPid(type),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### 2.4 Error Codes Extension (`src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`)\n\n**新增错误码**:\n\n```javascript\nexport const INFRA_ERROR_CODES = Object.freeze({\n  // Existing\n  CONFIG_MISSING: 'CONFIG_MISSING',\n  CONFIG_INVALID: 'CONFIG_INVALID',\n  PATH_INVALID: 'PATH_INVALID',\n  SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND: 'SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND',\n  EXEC_TIMEOUT: 'EXEC_TIMEOUT',\n  EXEC_FAILED: 'EXEC_FAILED',\n  \n  // NEW for F-004\n  LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED: 'LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED',\n  ALREADY_STOPPED: 'ALREADY_STOPPED',\n  PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING: 'PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING',\n  INVALID_TARGET: 'INVALID_TARGET',\n  TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE: 'TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE',\n  DAEMON_START_FAILED: 'DAEMON_START_FAILED',\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Interface Design\n\n### 3.1 Pipeline Controller API\n\n#### `startPipeline(params)`\n\n**Input**:\n```typescript\ninterface StartPipelineParams {\n  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  targetId?: string;        // Optional: start with specific target\n  listPath?: string;        // Optional: override default list path\n  daemon?: boolean;         // Default: true for startPipeline\n  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n  timeoutMs?: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface PipelineResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  runId?: string;\n  pid?: number;\n  message: string;\n  errorCode?: string;\n  hint?: string;\n  context?: Record<string, unknown>;\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Acquire lock for pipeline type\n2. If daemon mode, call `launch-daemon.sh start`\n3. If foreground, call `run.sh run [targetId]`\n4. Return result with PID (daemon) or execution result (foreground)\n\n---\n\n#### `stopPipeline(params)`\n\n**Input**:\n```typescript\ninterface StopPipelineParams {\n  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  timeoutMs?: number;       // Default: 10000\n}\n```\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface StopResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  previousPid?: number;\n  message: string;\n  errorCode?: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Check if daemon is running\n2. Call `launch-daemon.sh stop`\n3. Wait for process termination (with timeout)\n4. Release lock\n5. Return previous PID and status\n\n---\n\n#### `retryTarget(params)`\n\n**Input**:\n```typescript\ninterface RetryTargetParams {\n  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  targetId: string;\n  listPath?: string;\n  daemon?: boolean;\n  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n}\n```\n\n**Output**: Same as `startPipeline()`\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Validate target exists and is retryable\n2. If daemon mode, acquire lock first\n3. Execute retry script\n4. Return result\n\n---\n\n#### `runSingle(params)`\n\n**Input**:\n```typescript\ninterface RunSingleParams {\n  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  targetId: string;\n  listPath?: string;\n  timeoutMs?: number;\n  envOverrides?: Record<string, string>;\n}\n```\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface RunSingleResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  targetId: string;\n  message: string;\n  stdout?: string;\n  stderr?: string;\n  exitCode?: number;\n  errorCode?: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Execute single target in foreground\n2. Do NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n3. Return full execution details\n\n---\n\n#### `getStatus(params)`\n\n**Input**:\n```typescript\ninterface GetStatusParams {\n  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n}\n```\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface StatusResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  isRunning: boolean;\n  pid?: number;\n  currentFeature?: string;\n  startedAt?: string;\n  lastResult?: LastResult;\n  lockInfo?: LockInfo;\n  message: string;\n}\n\ninterface LastResult {\n  runId: string;\n  completedAt: string;\n  status: 'success' | 'failed' | 'partial';\n  featuresTotal: number;\n  featuresCompleted: number;\n}\n\ninterface LockInfo {\n  pid: number;\n  acquiredAt: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `getLogs(params)`\n\n**Input**:\n```typescript\ninterface GetLogsParams {\n  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n  lines?: number;           // Default: 100\n  follow?: boolean;         // Not implemented in v1\n}\n```\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface LogsResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  logs: string;\n  logPath: string;\n  lines: number;\n  message: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `forceUnlock(params)`\n\n**Input**:\n```typescript\ninterface ForceUnlockParams {\n  type: 'feature' | 'bugfix';\n}\n```\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface ForceUnlockResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  previousPid?: number;\n  message: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Get lock info\n2. Remove lock file\n3. Return previous lock info\n\n---\n\n### 3.2 Lock Manager API\n\n#### `acquireLock(type, pid?)`\n\n**Input**:\n- `type`: 'feature' | 'bugfix'\n- `pid`: number (default: process.pid)\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface LockResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  lockPath: string;\n  errorCode?: 'LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED';\n  currentHolder?: LockInfo;\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation**:\n1. Check if lock file exists\n2. If exists, validate PID is dead\n3. Write lock file atomically\n4. Return result\n\n---\n\n### 3.3 State Manager API\n\n#### `readDaemonMeta(type)`\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface DaemonMeta {\n  pid: number;\n  started_at: string;\n  feature_list: string;\n  env_overrides: string;\n  log_file: string;\n}\n```\n\n#### `readPipelineState(type)`\n\n**Output**:\n```typescript\ninterface PipelineState {\n  run_id: string;\n  status: 'running' | 'paused' | 'completed' | 'failed';\n  feature_list_path: string;\n  created_at: string;\n  total_features: number;\n  completed_features: number;\n  paused_at?: string;\n}\n```\n\n#### `isDaemonRunning(type)`\n\n**Output**: `boolean`\n\n**Implementation**:\n1. Read daemon meta\n2. Check if PID is alive via `process.kill(pid, 0)`\n3. Return boolean\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Model\n\n### 4.1 Lock File Schema\n\n**Path**: `{stateDir}/.pipeline.lock` or `bugfix-state/.pipeline.lock`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pid\": 12345,\n  \"acquiredAt\": \"2026-03-12T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"type\": \"feature\",\n  \"hostname\": \"dev-machine\"\n}\n```\n\n### 4.2 Last Result Schema (NEW)\n\n**Path**: `{stateDir}/.last-result.json` or `bugfix-state/.last-result.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"runId\": \"run-20260312-103000\",\n  \"completedAt\": \"2026-03-12T12:45:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"featuresTotal\": 8,\n  \"featuresCompleted\": 8,\n  \"exitCode\": 0,\n  \"message\": \"Pipeline completed successfully\"\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 State File Integration\n\nReuse existing state files:\n- `state/pipeline.json` → `readPipelineState('feature')`\n- `state/.pipeline-meta.json` → `readDaemonMeta('feature')`\n- `state/current-session.json` → `readCurrentSession('feature')`\n- Mirror paths for `bugfix-state/`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Module Dependencies\n\n```\npipeline-controller.js\n    ├── lock-manager.js\n    ├── state-manager.js\n    ├── script-runner.js (existing)\n    ├── config-loader.js (existing)\n    └── error-codes.js (extended)\n\nlock-manager.js\n    ├── path-policy.js (existing)\n    └── config-loader.js (existing)\n\nstate-manager.js\n    ├── path-policy.js (existing)\n    └── config-loader.js (existing)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Tests\n\n| Module | Test File | Focus |\n|--------|-----------|-------|\n| lock-manager.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` | Lock acquire/release, PID validation, stale lock cleanup |\n| state-manager.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js` | State file reading, JSON parsing, missing file handling |\n| pipeline-controller.js | `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js` | All API methods, error handling, mock dependencies |\n| error-codes.js | `tests/pipeline-infra/error-codes.test.js` | Error code validation, error factory |\n\n### 6.2 Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n\n| Test Case | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| Full Lifecycle | startPipeline → getStatus → stopPipeline |\n| Lock Behavior | Concurrent start attempts, lock release on stop |\n| Error Recovery | Stop non-running pipeline, retry invalid target |\n| State Persistence | Verify state files after operations |\n| Daemon Mode | Start daemon, query PID, verify log output |\n\n### 6.3 Test Coverage Target\n\n- Core modules: > 90% branch coverage\n- Integration tests: All user stories covered\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Mitigation | Owner |\n|------|------------|-------|\n| Lock file corruption | Atomic write via temp file + rename, validate JSON on read | Dev |\n| PID reuse race condition | Include timestamp in lock, validate with short timeout | Dev |\n| Large log file blocking | Use `fs.createReadStream` with line limit | Dev |\n| Test environment isolation | Use temp directories for state files in tests | Dev |\n| Backward compatibility with existing scripts | No script modifications, only wrappers | Dev |\n\n---\n\n## 8. User Story to Component Mapping\n\n| User Story | Primary Component | Supporting Components |\n|------------|-------------------|----------------------|\n| US-1: Unified Pipeline Start | pipeline-controller.startPipeline() | lock-manager, script-runner |\n| US-2: Pipeline Stop | pipeline-controller.stopPipeline() | state-manager, lock-manager |\n| US-3: Target Retry | pipeline-controller.retryTarget() | script-runner, state-manager |\n| US-4: Run Single Feature | pipeline-controller.runSingle() | script-runner |\n| US-5: Status Query | pipeline-controller.getStatus() | state-manager, lock-manager |\n| US-6: Logs Query | pipeline-controller.getLogs() | state-manager |\n| US-7: Concurrency Protection | lock-manager | state-manager |\n| US-8: Error Mapping | error-codes.js (extended) | pipeline-controller |\n| US-9: Telegram Handler Integration | pipeline-controller API design | All |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n- Setup test infrastructure\n- Extend error codes\n- Create lock-manager\n- Create state-manager\n\n### Phase 2: Core Controller (T-010 ~ T-099)\n- Implement pipeline-controller skeleton\n- Implement each API method\n- Integrate with existing script-runner\n\n### Phase 3: User Story Implementation (T-100+)\n- US-1: startPipeline\n- US-2: stopPipeline\n- US-3: retryTarget\n- US-4: runSingle\n- US-5: getStatus\n- US-6: getLogs\n- US-7: Lock integration\n- US-8: Error mapping\n- US-9: Integration tests\n\n### Phase 4: Polish (T-900+)\n- Documentation updates\n- Performance optimization\n- Edge case handling\n\n---\n\n## 10. Key Decisions\n\n| ID | Decision | Rationale |\n|----|----------|-----------|\n| D1 | Separate lock-manager module | Single responsibility, easier testing |\n| D2 | File-based locks with PID validation | No external dependencies, simple and reliable |\n| D3 | Reuse existing state files | Backward compatible, no migration needed |\n| D4 | New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service | Clear separation, avoid breaking existing API |\n| D5 | runSingle does NOT acquire lock | Independent execution use case |\n| D6 | Last result stored in separate file | Don't modify existing state file schema |\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/004-pipeline-process-controller/plan.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":33422,"output_tokens":4024,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_ae3e7667d5ac48f881c2ce4c","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:39:20.520Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
