{"type":"user","uuid":"44b4261a-83a5-42bc-9126-a320718402dd","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_448bf20193214d7cbc38e3b9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed to perform the **prizmkit.analyze** cross-check. Let me compile the analysis report:\n\n---\n\n# 🔍 prizmkit.analyze — F-004 Cross-Document Consistency Report\n\n**Feature**: F-004 Pipeline Process Controller  \n**Slug**: `004-pipeline-process-controller`  \n**Analysis Date**: 2026-03-12  \n**Analyzer**: Reviewer Agent\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Analysis Summary\n\n| Detection Channel | Status | Findings |\n|-------------------|--------|----------|\n| 重复检测 | ✅ PASS | No significant redundancy |\n| 歧义检测 | ⚠️ WARN | 2 MEDIUM issues |\n| 不完整检测 | 🔴 FAIL | 3 HIGH issues |\n| Prizm 规则对齐 | ✅ PASS | Documents follow Prizm format |\n| 覆盖缺口 | ⚠️ WARN | 2 HIGH issues |\n| 不一致性 | 🔴 FAIL | 4 HIGH issues |\n\n---\n\n## 🔴 CRITICAL Issues: 0\n\nNone found.\n\n---\n\n## 🟠 HIGH Issues: 5\n\n### [H-1] Error Code Set Inconsistency\n\n**Location**: \n- `spec.md:117` (AC-8.2)\n- `plan.md:153-169` (error-codes.js extension)\n\n**Description**: Spec AC-8.2 defines 7 error codes, but plan defines 9 error codes with additional `TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE` and `DAEMON_START_FAILED`. Missing alignment between spec and plan.\n\n| Spec Error Codes (AC-8.2) | Plan Error Codes |\n|---------------------------|------------------|\n| LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED | LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED |\n| SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND | SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND |\n| EXEC_TIMEOUT | EXEC_TIMEOUT |\n| EXEC_FAILED | EXEC_FAILED |\n| INVALID_TARGET | INVALID_TARGET |\n| PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING | PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING |\n| ALREADY_STOPPED | ALREADY_STOPPED |\n| — | TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE |\n| — | DAEMON_START_FAILED |\n\n**Impact**: Spec compliance failure - implementation may include error codes not specified in acceptance criteria.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Update `spec.md:117` to include all 9 error codes, or remove `TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE` and `DAEMON_START_FAILED` from plan if not needed.\n\n---\n\n### [H-2] US-7 Test Coverage Gap — Missing forceUnlock Test\n\n**Location**: \n- `tasks.md:129` (T-174)\n\n**Description**: US-7 (Concurrency Protection) AC-7.4 defines `forceUnlock({ type })` as admin operation. However, T-174 only covers \"concurrent start attempts\" — missing explicit test for `forceUnlock` functionality.\n\n**Impact**: Incomplete test coverage for US-7 acceptance criteria.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Add new task:\n```\n- [ ] [T-175] Write integration test for forceUnlock — file: tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js\n```\n\n---\n\n### [H-3] Stop Pipeline Timeout Specification Gap\n\n**Location**: \n- `spec.md:34` (AC-2.3): \"停止操作有 10 秒超时，超时后强制终止\"\n- `plan.md:220`: `timeoutMs?: number; // Default: 10000`\n\n**Description**: Spec defines **10 seconds** as mandatory timeout. Plan defines it as **default** parameter, implying it can be overridden. No AC specifies override behavior.\n\n**Impact**: Implementation may allow bypassing the 10-second safety limit.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Either:\n1. Add AC to spec allowing timeout configuration, OR\n2. Change plan to hardcode 10-second timeout (remove `timeoutMs` parameter from `StopPipelineParams`)\n\n---\n\n### [H-4] Target Retry Validation Logic Undefined\n\n**Location**: \n- `spec.md:46-47` (AC-3.2): \"若目标不存在或状态不允许可重试，返回明确错误\"\n- `plan.md:257-261` (retryTarget Behavior): \"1. Validate target exists and is retryable\"\n\n**Description**: Spec says \"状态不允许可重试\" but doesn't define what states are retryable. Plan mentions `TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE` error code but retryability criteria are undefined.\n\n**Impact**: Developer must make undocumented assumptions about retry logic.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Add to `spec.md` Technical Notes:\n```markdown\n### Retryability Criteria\n- Feature is retryable if: status === 'failed' AND not in current running session\n- Bugfix is retryable if: status === 'failed' AND not in current running session\n```\n\n---\n\n### [H-5] Missing Integration Test Task for US-8\n\n**Location**: \n- `tasks.md:137` (T-184)\n\n**Description**: T-184 \"Write integration test for US-8\" is listed, but US-8 (Error Mapping) is a cross-cutting concern. Integration test should verify error codes across all operations, not as standalone test.\n\n**Impact**: Potential test duplication or missing error code verification.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Reframe T-184 as:\n```\n- [ ] [T-184] Verify all error codes are returned correctly across all operations — file: tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🟡 MEDIUM Issues: 3\n\n### [M-1] isDaemonRunning vs getDaemonPid Semantic Overlap\n\n**Location**: \n- `plan.md:442-449` (isDaemonRunning)\n- `spec.md:74-77` (AC-5.2, AC-5.3)\n\n**Description**: Plan defines `isDaemonRunning()` (returns boolean) and `getDaemonPid()` (returns number). But state-manager section only shows `isDaemonRunning` implementation detail. The relationship between these two methods is unclear — does `getDaemonPid` return null if not running?\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Add to plan state-manager API:\n```typescript\nasync getDaemonPid(type): Promise<number | null>\n// Returns null if daemon not running\n```\n\n---\n\n### [M-2] runSingle Lock Behavior Not Documented in Spec\n\n**Location**: \n- `plan.md:292-295` (runSingle Behavior): \"Do NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\"\n- `spec.md:60-63` (AC-4.4): \"不影响管道整体状态（独立执行）\"\n\n**Description**: Plan explicitly states \"Do NOT acquire lock\", but spec only says \"不影响管道整体状态\". The lock behavior is an implementation detail that should be specified for clarity.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Add to `spec.md:63`:\n```\n- AC-4.5: 执行时不获取管道锁（与 startPipeline 行为不同）\n```\n\n---\n\n### [M-3] Daemon Mode Default Ambiguity\n\n**Location**: \n- `plan.md:187`: `daemon?: boolean; // Default: true for startPipeline`\n- `spec.md:20`: No default specified\n\n**Description**: Plan specifies `daemon: true` as default for `startPipeline`, but spec doesn't document this behavior. User story should clarify default mode.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Add to `spec.md:21`:\n```\n- AC-1.5: 未指定 daemon 参数时，默认为 true（后台守护模式）\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔵 LOW Issues: 2\n\n### [L-1] Test Coverage Target Minor Discrepancy\n\n**Location**: \n- `spec.md:151`: \"测试覆盖率 > 90%\"\n- `plan.md:539`: \"Core modules: > 90% branch coverage\"\n\n**Description**: Spec says \"测试覆盖率\" (general), plan specifies \"branch coverage\". Different coverage metrics may lead to confusion.\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Align terminology: use \"分支覆盖率 > 90%\" in spec.\n\n---\n\n### [L-2] Task File Reference Inconsistency\n\n**Location**: `tasks.md:14` (T-009)\n\n**Description**: T-009 says \"Create path policy helpers for lock files and last-result\" but path-policy.js already exists. Should be \"Extend\" not \"Create\".\n\n**Fix Suggestion**: Change task description to:\n```\n- [ ] [T-009] Extend path-policy.js with lock file and last-result path helpers — file: src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📋 User Story Coverage Matrix\n\n| User Story | Spec ACs | Plan Methods | Tasks | Integration Test | Coverage |\n|------------|----------|--------------|-------|------------------|----------|\n| US-1: Start | 4 | ✅ startPipeline | T-100~T-109 | T-109 | ✅ Full |\n| US-2: Stop | 4 | ✅ stopPipeline | T-120~T-126 | T-126 | ✅ Full |\n| US-3: Retry | 4 | ✅ retryTarget | T-130~T-135 | T-135 | ⚠️ Partial (retry logic undefined) |\n| US-4: Single | 4 | ✅ runSingle | T-140~T-145 | T-145 | ✅ Full |\n| US-5: Status | 4 | ✅ getStatus | T-150~T-156 | T-156 | ✅ Full |\n| US-6: Logs | 4 | ✅ getLogs | T-160~T-165 | T-165 | ✅ Full |\n| US-7: Lock | 4 | ✅ lock-manager | T-170~T-174 | T-174 | ❌ Missing forceUnlock test |\n| US-8: Errors | 4 | ✅ error-codes | T-180~T-184 | T-184 | ⚠️ Error set mismatch |\n| US-9: Telegram | 4 | ✅ factory | T-190~T-196 | T-196 | ✅ Full |\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Final Verdict\n\n| Metric |