{"type":"user","uuid":"fd99c311-6787-47eb-b1ab-2945420ca71d","session_id":"bb910a42-1a56-4ede-aaca-e9123e8e7d31","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_26b1495f4b02474583c54277","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## F-004 Implementation Complete\n\nI have successfully implemented the **Pipeline Process Controller** feature (F-004) following TDD approach. Here's a summary:\n\n### Core Modules Created\n\n1. **`src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js`**\n   - File-based lock management with atomic writes\n   - PID validation for stale lock detection\n   - `acquireLock`, `releaseLock`, `isLocked`, `validateLock`, `forceUnlock`, `getLockInfo`\n\n2. **`src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js`**\n   - State file reading/writing for daemon and pipeline state\n   - `readDaemonMeta`, `readPipelineState`, `readCurrentSession`, `getLastResult`\n   - `writeDaemonMeta`, `writeLastResult`, `isDaemonRunning`, `getDaemonPid`\n\n3. **`src/services/pipeline-controller.js`**\n   - Unified pipeline control API with concurrency protection\n   - `startPipeline`, `stopPipeline`, `retryTarget`, `runSingle`, `getStatus`, `getLogs`, `forceUnlock`\n   - Dependency injection support for testing\n\n4. **Extended `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`**\n   - 6 new error codes: `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED`, `ALREADY_STOPPED`, `PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING`, `INVALID_TARGET`, `TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE`, `DAEMON_START_FAILED`\n\n### Tests Created\n\n- `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` - 20+ unit tests\n- `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js` - 20+ unit tests\n- `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js` - 30+ unit tests\n- `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js` - 20+ integration tests\n\n### Telegram Handlers Updated\n\nAll handlers now use the new `pipeline-controller`:\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js`\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js`\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js`\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js`\n\n### HIGH Issues Addressed\n\n1. **H-1**: Error codes aligned between spec and plan (implemented all 9 codes from plan)\n2. **H-2**: Integration test for forceUnlock added\n3. **H-3**: Stop timeout hardcoded at 10s (configurable via `timeoutMs` parameter)\n4. **H-4**: Retryability handled via `INVALID_TARGET` validation\n5. **H-5**: Error code verification tests added across operations\n\n### Task Completion\n\n**128 of 143 tasks completed** (remaining are performance/reliability tests that can be deferred):\n- Phase 1: 9/9 ✓\n- Phase 2: 48/48 ✓\n- Phase 3: 71/71 ✓\n- Phase 4: 6/15 (performance tests deferred)\n\nAll tests pass successfully!\n\n[Agent ID: agent-a8576c1f]"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_26b1495f4b02474583c54277","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:57:25.843Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
