lineCommand(req)\n  38→- buildPipelineCommand(req, config) -> { command, args }\n  39→- createLockManager(options?) -> F-004 lock manager instance\n  40→- createStateManager(options?) -> F-004 state manager instance\n  41→\n  42→SERVICE_LAYER: src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  43→SERVICE_TESTS: tests/services/pipeline-control-service.test.js\n  44→\n  45→ERROR_MODEL:\n  46→- codes: CONFIG_MISSING, CONFIG_INVALID, PATH_INVALID, SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND, EXEC_TIMEOUT, EXEC_FAILED\n  47→- F-004 codes: LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED, ALREADY_STOPPED, PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING, INVALID_TARGET, TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE, DAEMON_START_FAILED\n  48→- createInfraError(code, message, { hint, context }) -> serializable infra error payload\n  49→\n  50→TRAPS:\n  51→- keep path_policy.py and path-policy.js behavior aligned (slug + session paths + daemon logs)\n  52→- avoid breaking existing run.sh/run-bugfix.sh CLI contracts\n  53→- request validation must reject unknown pipelineType/action and missing targetId for retry/reset\n  54→- lock files must use atomic write (temp file + rename) to prevent corruption\n  55→- PID validation must check process alive with process.kill(pid, 0) + ESRCH catch\n  56→\n  57→DECISIONS:\n  58→- 2026-03-10 | f001-js-path-policy | include explicit daemon log policy resolver for US2 coverage\n  59→- 2026-03-10 | f001-runner-actions | treat logs/reset as first-class runner actions for US3 coverage\n  60→- 2026-03-12 | f001-feature-complete | all US1-US4 acceptance criteria verified via integration tests\n  61→- 2026-03-12 | f004-lock-manager | file lock + PID validation for concurrency protection (D1)\n  62→- 2026-03-12 | f004-state-manager | separate module for state file management (D2)\n  63→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_90575598e7484a1399e96872","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T19:59:48.481Z","_requestId":"deb8a7f51c6541338686a9cbc6281864"}
